PN,41203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1781700487
OL,3,CComplainants in Donaldson case 'not
OL,4,Creliable enough' for guilty verdict-
OL,5,C defence
OL,7,FJeffrey Donaldson spent two days in
OL,8,Fthe witness box giving evidence in the
OL,9,Ftrial last week.
OL,11,FLady Eleanor Donaldson denies several
OL,12,Fcharges of aiding and abetting her
OL,13,Fhusband's alleged offending.
OL,15,FShe is facing a trial of the facts on
OL,16,Fmental health grounds.
OL,18,FThe trial of the facts will test the
OL,19,Fevidence in the case but cannot result
OL,20,Fin a criminal conviction.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
